s and surveys of relevant material, allowing for in-depth analyses of the terracottas in those life stages of shifting contextual interactions. The approach furthers new knowledge on several levels, such as the value of the terracottas, their suitability and their popularity as dedications, their iconography and symbolism, the general votive practice, and the end of the terracotta practice. As such, the book is relevant for all who seek insights on terracotta figurines, votive offerings, ritual practice, as well as those interested in archaeological methodology, theory and contexts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGoddesses, Greek, in art. 0aGods, Greek, in art. 0aTerra-cotta sculpture, GreekxReligious aspects. 0aVotive offeringszGreece. 4aGriechenland (Altertum). 4aHerstellungskette. 4aTerrakottafiguren. 4aWeihgabe. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh  aChaîne opératoire.  aGreek terracotta figurines.  aGreek votive offerings.  aRitual votive practice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023 Englishz978311131908708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311076887940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311077022340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110770223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110770223/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131908-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical 